<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Craig</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">It sounds like I am definitely in the minority but I like pickup groups. Sure a quarter to a third of them really suck but the good ones more than make for that. I really meeting new people all the time, I've made some really good friends this way. And I've learned how to handle many different situations, I don't think theres a combinations of classes I haven't grouped with. I do agree that you (generally) have better luck getting good groups the higher up in level you go.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jerricoe</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Pickup groups are generally a great way to meet new people, some good, some bad. But you soon learn who the bad ones are and stay clear of them.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>------------------<BR>Jerricoe Seer<BR>High Priest<BR><A HREF="http://www.redskyeq.com" TARGET=_blank>Red Sky</A> - Bertoxxulous</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Josiefuz</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I love pickup groups.  I get 10x the xp and loot in pickup groups that I get in a guild group.  <P>The reason xp sucks with guild groups:<P>1.  Everytime you have 6 people who can work together someone says, "Wow, we should go to <zone> and kill <mob> for <loot/quest>".  Then we spend an hour getting to the new zone when someone has to log, and our group falls apart.<P>2.  "Gee, we should go raid <zone>".  So you go from 6 people getting xp to 30 people getting no xp.<P>The reason loot sucks in guild groups:<P>1.  Need before greed.<P>2.  Hand-me-downs expected<P>Pickup groups for profit and xp.  Guild groups for fun with friends.<P>-Fuz<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jerricoe</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Couldn't agree more Fuz.<BR>Pickup groups for cash and loot.<BR>However some of my best exp groups have been all guild groups.<BR>Knowing the people and knowing that they can play their class well lets you really push that single group thing.<P>------------------<BR>Jerricoe Seer<BR>High Priest<BR><A HREF="http://www.redskyeq.com" TARGET=_blank>Red Sky</A> - Bertoxxulous<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=15665" TARGET=_blank>Profile</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Merridith_UK</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gosh, god forbid helping all those folks who've helped you get your armour and spells and what not. <P>Cos profits better playing with strangers...</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Josiefuz</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Raids are for benefitting the guild not pickup groups.  I raid more than my share already to help the guild as a whole.  <P>I was referring to pickup groups for xp and profit.  Besides, just because people aren't in your guild doesn't mean they're strangers.  I've got hundreds of non-guild friends in Norrath.<P>-Fuz<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Josiefuz</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Oh, and to the "Gosh, god forbid helping all those folks who've helped you get your armour and spells and what not." comment:  <P>Aside from EM legs and my epic, everything else I own, including all my 55+ spells, came from pickup groups or from trading items won in pickup groups.  It took me 3 fungi tunics to pay for all my spells.  <P>Don't get me wrong, I love my guild.  But it's my responsibility to equip myself, not my guild's.<P>-Fuz<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Merridith_UK</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">More power to you if you need to make your own way, but come on, you didnt honestly expect to say 'NBG and hand me downs in guild groups sucks' and not have someone comment on it. <P>Surely the best thing about guild groups is that you *can* go NBG and you do get hand me downs and the best thing about pickup groups is that (if agreed) you *can* roll on stuff in order to sell it.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Twinskey Bab0linskey</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I love pick up groups and xp'ing.<P>I don't buy anything, so lewt is not a major issue... but I enjoy the fact that pick-up groups are usually quicker to start and Fuz is right... it's very very rare that someone says "Hey, I need to go kill........" and expects you to come help.<P>I'll go to my grave wondering how I'm the greedy one if I don't want to go get "you" an item.... it seems more like the other person's being greedy, but that's just me.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Josiefuz</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">NBG is great, except that most drops are not for clerics.  So in order for me to get better gear, I tend to have to buy it.  In order to buy it, I have to have something worth selling.<P>As for hand-me-downs...hmm where to begin...  I currently wear a emerald dragon bp that I bought for 40k.  I currently have about 2k in the bank.  If I won a velious BP on a raid, I'll not be handing down my emerald dragon bp.  Expected or not, forget it.  That 40k will buy me a horse + 2 tink bags + cash in the bank for spells.  That's not greed, that's just economics.<P>Now, if I had gotten that dragon bp from a guild raid, then I would definately consider handing it down, because the guild helped earn it.  As it was, I had to spend long hours kicking Fungi arse to raise money to buy it.<P>Others may disagree, but this is my stance.<P>-Fuz<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">NightGod</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I agree totally Fuz...I give nice discounts to guildies who want to buy stuff I bought with my own cash when I get a replacement (and on drops I get in non-guild groups), but I don't give away stuff. If I got a drop during an all (or mostly) guild event, then later get an upgrade (without paying for it outta my own cash), yeah, of course I hand it down, but if it's something I busted my hump to afford, sorry guys, you gotta pay just like I did...<P>------------------<BR>Higar Mettlebender<BR>Vicar of the 52nd Prayer and Luclin Loot Ho<BR>Weilder of the Water Sprinkler of Nem`Ankh<BR>Guardians of the Keep<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=20669" TARGET=_blank>Higar's Profile</A><BR>Master Drinker (200) <BR>Master Jeweler (188)Master Fletcher (185)Master Brewer (175) Master Smith (175) Master Potter (168) Master Baker (162) (Anyone got any dragon meat lying around??) Master Tailor (161)<BR>Proud wearer of the 7th prayer shawl.<BR>Coldfyre <BR>Warrior of the 14th Blade<BR>Grandmaster Mule (255) Grandmaster Trader (255) <P>Drinal Server <BR>"These balls are making me testy!"</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Taishar Malkier</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">if at any time u receive an item from a guild raid, or through guild indirectly, and will not be using that item on ur main for any reason, you should return it to guild.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Windeliane</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Josiefuz's point of view is also mine. I sometimes give some stuff i win in pickup group to guildies, but it's my choice to sell it or not. We need money too !!<P>Of course, guild raid stuff belongs to the guild.<P>Anyway, i love pickup groups  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"> they allow you to make new friends, even if some groupmates are sometimes not worth beeing know  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/tongue.gif"><P>I won't apply NBG in a pickup group. Josie is also right here : too few cleric drops imho.<P><P>------------------<BR>Windeliane<BR>Healer of the 58th circle<BR>Member of L'Ordre du Phoenix on Terris-Thule</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Josiefuz</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Heh, I had some hot dice last night!  I was in a pickup group in Maiden's eye and picked up these:<P>Medallion of Life (5 str, 50 mana, +5 all resists, no drop)<P>Shaded staff (10/22, +5 all resists, 1hb all/all, droppable)<P>Shrouded boots (ac 12, all stats +4)<P>These dropped over an 8 hour xp grind.  It was a good nite!  The medallion replaced my goblin soul caller I've had for the last 30 levels, the staff is merchant bait but I'll probably sell it to a guildy (usually I sell to guild for half the market price unless I need cash for something), the boots became my feet-swappers with donals for those times when I need the wis/charisma more than ac.<P>By the way: 8 hours of straight xp with no deaths and consistantly good groups in maiden's eye = 1.6 blue bubbles /cry.. 59 sucks!<P>-Fuz<BR>59 Templar, Sol Ro<BR></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
